HEADWORD: Disformity
<hw>Dis*form"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Deformity</er>.]</ety> <def>Discordance or diversity of form;
unlikeness in form.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Uniformity or <qex>disformity</qex> in comparing together the
respective figures of bodies.</q> <rj><qau>S. Clarke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

